318&wc=MKZ4-RMW%3A1004777901%2C1004790201|title=Maryland, Baltimore Passenger Lists, 1820-1948|last=Sevcik|date=1882|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Frantisek (1875-1964),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/3:1:3QS7-99Z8-TJH6?cc=2018318&wc=MKZ4-RMW%3A1004777901%2C1004790201|title=Maryland, Baltimore Passenger Lists, 1820-1948|last=Sevcik|date=1882|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nSramek - Barbora (1838-1926) [wife of Jan Sevcik],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/3:1:3QS7-99Z8-TJH6?cc=2018318&wc=MKZ4-RMW%3A1004777901%2C1004790201|title=Maryland, Baltimore Passenger Lists, 1820-1948|last=Sramek|date=1882|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Terezie (1872-1970),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/3:1:3QS7-99Z8-TJH6?cc=2018318&wc=MKZ4-RMW%3A1004777901%2C1004790201|title=Maryland, Baltimore Passenger Lists, 1820-1948|last=Sramek|date=1882|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|[[File:Charles Duban (1867-1914).png|center|thumb|181x181px|Charles Duban (1867-1914)]]\n|-\n|SS Hohenstaufen\n\nBremen\n|27 April 1883\nBaltimore\n|Duban - Emanuel (1858-1943) [temporarily returned had a son who might've been born in Mysliv, then went back to America],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:QK6L-6W2G|title=Maryland, Baltimore Passenger Lists, 1820-1948|last=Duban|date=1883|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nKolarik - Frantisek (1868-1951),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:QK6L-6W2P|title=Maryland, Baltimore Passenger Lists, 1820-1948|last=Kolarik|date=1883|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nSramek - Frantiska (1852-1924) [with her husband from Nehodiv, Frantisek Koncal, 