le: The Cultural Hybridity of White Rastafarians |journal=Glocalism: Journal of Culture, Politics and Innovation |year=2013 |pages=1\u201321 |volume=1 |issue=2013, 1 |doi=10.12893/gjcpi.2013.1.1 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=MacLeod |first=Erin C. |title=Visions of Zion: Ethiopians and Rastafari in the Search for the Promised Land |year=2014 |location=New York and London |publisher=New York University Press |isbn=978-1479882243 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Merritt |first=Anthony |title=How Can We Sing King Alpha's Song in a Strange Land?: The Sacred Music of the Boboshanti Rastafari |journal=Journal of Africana Religions|volume=5 |number=2 |year=2017 |pages=282\u2013291 |doi= 10.5325/jafrireli.5.2.0282 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Mhango |first=Mtendeweka Owen |title=The Constitutional Protection of Minority Religious Rights in Malawi: The Case of Rastafari Students |journal=Journal of African Law |volume=52 |number=2 |year=2008 |pages=218\u2013244 |jstor=27608008 |ref=harv|doi=10.1017/S0021855308000107 }}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Middleton |first=Darren J. N. |title=As it is in Zion: Seeking the Rastafari in Ghana, West Africa |journal=Black Theology |volume=4 |issue=2 |pages=151\u2013172 |year=2006 |doi=10.1558/blth.2006.4.2.151 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Newland |first=Arthur |title=Rastafari in the Grenada Revolution |journal=Social and Economic Studies |volume=62 |number=3 |year=2013 |pages=205\u2013226 |jstor=24384487 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Partridge |first=Christopher |year=2004 |title=The Re-Enchantment of the West Volume. 1: Alternative Spiritualities, Sacralization, Popular Culture, and Occulture |publisher=T&T Clark International |location=London |isbn=978-0567084088 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Pereira |first=Joseph |title=Babylon to Vatican: Religion in the Dance Hall |journal=Journal of West Indian Literature |volume=8 |number=1 |year=1998 |pages=31\u201340 |jstor=23019814 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite 