rin |title=Rasta, Race and Revolution: Transnational Connections in Socialist Cuba |year=2001 |journal=Journal of Ethnic and Migration Studies |volume=27 |issue=4 |pages=733\u2013747 |doi=10.1080/13691830120090476 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Hansing |first=Katrin |title=Rastafari in a Different Kind of Babylon: The Emergence and Development of the Rastafari Movement in Socialist Cuba |journal=Caribbean Studies |volume=34 |number=1 |year=2006 |pages=61\u201384 |jstor=25613510 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Ifekwe |first=B. Steiner |title=Rastafarianism in Jamaica as a Pan-African Protest Movement |journal=Journal of the Historical Society of Nigeria |volume=17 |year=2008 |pages=106\u2013122 |jstor=41857150 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite journal |first1=Alemseghed |last1=Kebede |last2=Knottnerus |first2=J. David |year=1998 |title=Beyond the Pales of Babylon: The Ideational Components and Social Psychological Foundations of Rastafari |journal=Sociological Perspectives |volume=41 |issue=3 |pages=499\u2013517 |jstor=1389561 |ref=harv |doi=10.2307/1389561 }}\n\n: {{cite journal |first=Stephen A. |last=King |year=1998 |title=International Reggae, Democratic Socialism, and the Secularization of the Rastafarian Movement, 1972\u20131980 |journal=Popular Music and Society |volume=22 |issue=3 |pages=39\u201360 |doi=10.1080/03007769808591713 |ref=harv|url=https://thekeep.eiu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1011&context=commstudies_fac }}\n\n: {{cite book |last=King |first=Stephen A. |title=Reggae, Rastafari, and the Rhetoric of Social Control |publisher=University Press of Mississippi |location=Jackson |year=2002 |isbn=978-1604730036 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Kitzinger |first=Sheila |title=The Rastafarian Brethren of Jamaica |journal=Comparative Studies in Society and History |volume=9 |issue=1 |year=1966 |pages=33\u201339 |jstor=177835 |ref=harv|doi=10.1017/S0010417500004321 }}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Kitzinger |first=Sheila |title=Protest and Mysticism: